For some reason whois fails for some time on T2 (vanilla source)
systems like:

getaddrinfo( ... ): Bad value for ai_flags

Don't use getaddrinfo until this is fully debugged.

  - Rene Rebe <rene@exactcode.de>

--- whois-4.7.26/config.h.vanilla	2008-07-01 20:18:57.000000000 +0200
+++ whois-4.7.26/config.h	2008-07-01 20:19:22.000000000 +0200
@@ -37,7 +37,7 @@
 #if defined __GLIBC__
 # define HAVE_GETOPT_LONG
 # if __GLIBC__ >= 2 && __GLIBC_MINOR__ >= 1
-#  define HAVE_GETADDRINFO
+#  /*define HAVE_GETADDRINFO */
 # endif
 # if __GLIBC__ >= 2 && __GLIBC_MINOR__ >= 7
 #  define HAVE_SHA_CRYPT
